	 <section id="section_288CC85536684C2DB184141358481EF0"> 
		<title>Example Pages Report</title> 
		<p>An example of a Pages Report (<uicontrol>View All Reports</uicontrol>
		  &gt; 
		  <uicontrol>Site Content</uicontrol> &gt; 
		  <uicontrol>Pages Reports</uicontrol> &gt; 
		  <uicontrol>Pages</uicontrol>). 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <image placement="break" align="center"
			href="graphics/pages_report.png" width="672px"
			id="image_151E845BFF96442E86C7F2F0D03D336C"></image> 
		</p> 
	 </section> 
	 <section id="section_0D674177AE6C4A71B07234DB25910ECD"> 
		<title>Report Toolbar</title> 
		<p>Share your report data with the decision makers who can change your
		  site or marketing strategies based on the data. For more information, see a
		  description of the 
		  <xref
			href="c_improved_navigation.xml#concept_B2F59AF1E3554F37A22D2ACB6210B8F6"
			format="dita" scope="local">Reports Menu</xref>.
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <image href="graphics/toolbar.png"
			id="image_5EA6C129B4AB4CF5897DF90F50ED3153" width="672px"></image> 
		</p> 
		<p>Also refer to 
		  <xref
			href="reports_customize.xml#concept_F042066264564438BFB35FC46EB638DF"
			type="concept" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Customizing a Report?></xref>.
		  
		</p> 
	 </section> 
	 <section id="section_12A90FAE02EC43FB9F11F0E2CE8FAE8F"> 
		<title>Report Header &amp; Settings</title> 
		<p>Displays report settings and lets you configure the report type,
		  select metrics, and more. The available options in this group changes depending
		  on the report you run. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <image href="graphics/settings_header.png"
			id="image_4D728B382E8D4A2EB6CB51E742A595CD"></image> 
		</p>See 
		<xref
		 href="reports_customize.xml#concept_F042066264564438BFB35FC46EB638DF"
		 type="concept" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Customizing a Report?></xref>
		for more information. 
	 </section> 
	 <section id="section_8C6C4AD84D9043E8ABD53FF8F645AAB1"> 
		<title>Calendar</title> 
		<p>Specify the date by clicking the calendar button and selecting a date
		  range. You can also select two time ranges to compare performance. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <image href="graphics/calendar_large.png"
			id="image_98313A39CDC8469389EA9330499BE33D" width="672px"></image> 
		</p> 
		<p>See 
		  <xref
			href="t_reports_select_date.xml#task_9BEF7D4D839A4748B76E8500D1406C34"
			type="task" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Selecting a Date or Date Range?></xref>
		  and 
		  <xref
			href="t_reports_comparing_dates.xml#task_95155C3700774B709F5FB81AE96B0824"
			type="task" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Comparing Dates?></xref>.
		  
		</p> 
	 </section> 
	 <section id="section_8B9CBA4096E64FC3B744E2E06EB83C19"> 
		<title>Graph Type</title> 
		<p>Select the type of graph or chart you want to see. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <image href="graphics/graph_type.png"
			id="image_F4D5848D04E74EB098128279D188E7A9"></image> 
		</p>See 
		<xref href="t_reports_graphs.xml#task_B290BF0B82124111AA19B3F3ACED500A"
		 type="task" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Changing Report Graphs?></xref>.
		
	 </section> 
	 <section id="section_4C78ADC82C234CC6841AC92C803636F4"> 
		<title>Graph Display</title> 
		<p>Depending on the type of graph that you have selected, you typically
		  see the top several items from the details list. If your graph is a trended
		  graph showing different time periods, then all of the time periods display 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <image href="graphics/graph.png"
			id="image_58AC6185D4454961B292FDB95FB4EADB"></image> 
		</p> 
		<p>See 
		  <xref
			href="reports_customize.xml#concept_F042066264564438BFB35FC46EB638DF"
			format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Customizing Reports?></xref>. 
		</p> 
	 </section> 
	 <section id="section_8B8F9EC72B864E29B91039E7B7381EAD"> 
		<title>Metrics</title> 
		<p>Add metrics to your report. Administrators can specify default
		  metrics. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <image href="graphics/metrics.png"
			id="image_8C97EB887B1944728EAA262F27510C3D"></image> 
		</p> 
		<p>See 
		  <xref href="metrics.xml#concept_EB00207C07BD4481AB116E62EC24E686"
			format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Metrics?></xref>. 
		</p> 
	 </section> 
	 <section id="section_449A5DC848744F65A10DA12E189B835D"> 
		<title>Detail Table</title> 
		<p>The details are the bulk of the report data. In this case, you have
		  pages listed, and they are being measured by Page Views, which is how many
		  times they were loaded during the period. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <image href="graphics/detail.png"
			id="image_FFA1EA3CA37945E494B983B20042D4FE"></image> 
		</p> 
		<p>In the detail table, you can filter data, create breakdowns, add
		  metrics, and more. 
		</p> 
		<p>See 
		  <xref
			href="reports_customize.xml#concept_F042066264564438BFB35FC46EB638DF"
			format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Customizing Reports?></xref>. 
		</p> 
	 </section> 
